# Sona Emotion Module Specification v1.0
**Target Release:** Sona 1.0.0 — April 18th  
**Author:** Andre D. Bryant, Waycore Inc.  
**Status:** Locked — Implementation Ready

---

## Overview

The Sona `emotion` module is a deterministic, auditable emotional awareness system built into the Sona standard library. It detects emotional states from developer inputs, runtime behavior, API patterns, and code structure — and responds with deterministic, policy-governed strategies. Every detection event is logged as a first-class receipt entry, making emotional reasoning fully replayable and explainable.

The core principle: **same input, same state, same response, same receipt. Always.**

---

## Architecture

```
[ Input Sources ]
      │
      ▼
[ Emotion Backends ]  ←  rule-based (default) | openai | ollama | custom
      │
      ▼
[ Detection Engine ]  ←  per-source detection → composite resolution
      │
      ▼
[ Response Mapper ]   ←  state × intensity → strategy (deterministic)
      │
      ▼
[ Receipt Logger ]    ←  tamper-evident, signed, auditable
```

The backend is a pluggable interface. Sona ships with a rule-based default backend that requires no API key or model. External inference backends (OpenAI, Ollama, custom) can be swapped in via configuration without changing any Sona code.

---

## Core State Taxonomy (1.0.0)

Six primary emotional states form the 1.0.0 core. These are stable, versioned constants in the Sona type system. Adding new states requires a plugin — the core six are frozen at 1.0.0.

| State | Description | Primary Domain |
|---|---|---|
| `FRUSTRATED` | Repeated failure, blocked progress, error loops | Developer, Customer |
| `CONFUSED` | Unclear input, inconsistent patterns, repeated clarification | All |
| `FOCUSED` | Clean structure, steady progress, low error rate | Developer, General |
| `OVERWHELMED` | Too many inputs, cascading errors, complexity spike | All |
| `DISENGAGED` | Long inactivity, shallow patterns, minimal output | Developer, Customer |
| `CONFIDENT` | Consistent success, clean code, fast resolution | All |

### Out of Scope (1.0.0 Core)

`DISTRESSED` — crisis-level emotional signals — is intentionally excluded from the core module due to legal and clinical sensitivity. It ships as `emotion-plugin-distressed`, a separately installed opt-in plugin with its own policy gates.

